=========================================================
OPERATOR OVERLOADING IN C++ (INTERVIEW NOTES)
=========================================================

Definition:
Operator Overloading allows existing operators to work with
user-defined types (classes/objects).

It is an example of:

Compile-Time Polymorphism
(Early Binding / Static Binding)

=========================================================
WHY DO WE NEED OPERATOR OVERLOADING?
=========================================================

Without Operator Overloading:

Complex c3 = c1.add(c2);

With Operator Overloading:

Complex c3 = c1 + c2;

Makes code:
• More readable
• More intuitive
• Similar to built-in types

